text.section:
The Board shall reinstate the license of a nursing home administrator who has failed to renew the license for any reason, if the licensee:
Has not had the license suspended or revoked;
Meets the renewal requirements of § 9-311 of this subtitle;
Pays to the Board the reinstatement fee set by the Board;
Submits to the Board satisfactory evidence of compliance with the qualifications and requirements established under this title for license reinstatements; and
Applies to the Board for reinstatement of the license within 5 years after the license expires.
